id: monica-bun-dependabot
title: Fixed Dependabot updates so bun.lock is maintained
description: The npm ecosystem updater creates package-lock.json changes while the required Bun frozen install consumes bun.lock.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[4]: automation,bun,ci,dependabot
created_at: "2026-07-16T16:58:08.386Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-21T17:27:11.432Z"
deadline: "2026-07-18T16:58:08.386Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-16T17:19:29.667Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 120
acceptance_criteria: Dependabot uses Bun ecosystem support; dependency PRs update bun.lock; CI does not create or rely on package-lock.json
definition_of_ready: Failure log and official ecosystem support are confirmed.
parent: monica-security-modernization
reviewer: unbraind
risk: high
confidence: 100
sprint: 2026-07-security-modernization
release: next
reporter: Repository audit
severity: high
environment: GitHub Actions Dependabot pull requests
repro_steps: "Open any npm Dependabot PR and inspect Validate (Bun): lockfile had changes but lockfile is frozen."
resolution: "Changed Dependabot to package-ecosystem bun, retained bun.lock as authoritative, grouped compatible updates, and added explicit ignores for unsupported compiler/runtime type majors."
expected_result: Automated dependency PRs update bun.lock and pass frozen Bun installation.
actual_result: Native Bun PRs #48 and #49 updated bun.lock and executed Bun validation; scoped ignores now prevent known-incompatible majors from reopening.
affected_version: 2026.3.6-2
component: dependency-automation
regression: false
customer_impact: Security and maintenance updates remain unmergeable.
